\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Place silicone pad on a cookie sheet.\
Place chocolate in a double boiler and melt over simmering water.\
Put butter, sugar, and water in a heavy pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Bring to a bubbling boil, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, about 10 minutes. Remove spoon from pan, and cook to a very brittle stage (300 degrees to 310 degrees F on a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/candyfat-thermometer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 candy thermometer}}). Or, make a cold water test: candy will separate into hard, brittle threads when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat and add almonds to mixture. Add vanilla and salt. Pour onto prepared {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cookie/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cookie}} sheet and spread to 1/4-inch thickness. Cool slightly.\
Spread a thin layer of melted chocolate over toffee layer. Cool completely and break into pieces. Store in an airtight container.\
Variation: Toasted almonds may be sprinkled over  melted chocolate instead of added to toffee.}